      "content": "There is no single \"scientific consensus\" on how to handle gender identity in schools or medical care because the scientific community itself is deeply divided on the issue. While many experts agree that gender identity is real and distinct from sex assigned at birth, they disagree sharply on whether it should be treated as a medical condition requiring treatment or a natural variation of human experience. This fundamental disagreement means that policies in education and healthcare remain highly contested and vary widely across different countries and regions.",
